Enum ResourceToolAction.ActionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ResourceToolAction.ActionType>
      • org.sakaiproject.content.api.ResourceToolAction.ActionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ResourceToolAction.ActionType>
    Enclosing interface:
    ResourceToolAction

    public static enum ResourceToolAction.ActionType
extends Enum<ResourceToolAction.ActionType>
    ActionType defines identifiers for types of actions related to resources.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NEW_UPLOAD

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType NEW_UPLOAD
        Create upload -- Handled by Resources tool. Can create multiple uploads at once. Metadata and content supplied in same form. Requires content.new permission in parent folder.

      • NEW_FOLDER

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType NEW_FOLDER
        Create folder -- Handled by Resources tool. Can create multiple folders at once. No content; requires metadata only. Requires content.new permission in parent folder.

      • NEW_URLS

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType NEW_URLS
        Create URLs -- Handled by Resources tool. Can create multiple URLs at once. No content; requires metadata only. Requires content.new permission in parent folder.

      • CREATE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType CREATE
        Create other -- Handled by helper and Resources tool. Can create one item at a time. Content (and possibly some properties) handled by helper. Metadata supplied in form that appears after helper finishes. Requires content.new permission in parent folder.

      • DELETE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType DELETE
        Delete -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.delete permission

      • REVISE_CONTENT

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType REVISE_CONTENT
        Revise content -- Handled by helper. Requires content.revise.any permission (or content.revise.own if user is creator).

      • REPLACE_CONTENT

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType REPLACE_CONTENT
        Replace content -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.revise.any permission (or content.revise.own if user is creator).

      • REVISE_METADATA

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType REVISE_METADATA
        Revise metadata -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.revise.any permission (or content.revise.own if user is creator).

      • COPY

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType COPY
        Copy -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.read permission for item being copied and content.new permission in folder to which it's copied.

      • MOVE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType MOVE
        Move -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.delete (or content.update ?) permission for item being moved and content.new permission in folder to which it's moved.

      • DUPLICATE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType DUPLICATE
        Duplicate -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.read permission for item being duplicated and content.new permission in parent folder.

      • VIEW_CONTENT

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType VIEW_CONTENT
        View content -- Handled by AccessServlet (via Resources tool) or helper. Requires content.read permission.

      • VIEW_METADATA

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType VIEW_METADATA
        View metadata -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.read permission.

      • PASTE_MOVED

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType PASTE_MOVED
        Paste Moved Items -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.new permission. The action is only available after a MOVE action and before some other action that cancels the PASTE_MOVED.

      • PASTE_COPIED

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType PASTE_COPIED
        Paste Copied Items -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.new permission. The action is only available after a COPY action and before some other action that cancels the PASTE_COPIED.

      • REVISE_ORDER

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType REVISE_ORDER
        Defines a custom sort order for the contents of a folder -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires content.revise permission for the folder.

      • REVISE_PERMISSIONS

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType REVISE_PERMISSIONS
        Revise folder permissions -- Handled by Resources tool. Requires site.upd permission.

      • EXPAND_FOLDER

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType EXPAND_FOLDER
        Expand a folder to show its members -- Handled by Resources tool. Available to anybody with content.read permission for the contents of the folder.

      • COLLAPSE_FOLDER

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType COLLAPSE_FOLDER
        Collapse a folder to hide its members -- Handled by Resources tool. No permission checks.

      • CUSTOM_TOOL_ACTION

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType CUSTOM_TOOL_ACTION
        Custom action -- Handled by helper. May be interactive or service-level. Custom actions must implement the CustomToolAction interface to provide Resources tool with a way to determine permissions, as well as either InteractionAction or ServiceLevelAction.

      • COMPRESS_ZIP_FOLDER

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType COMPRESS_ZIP_FOLDER
        Compress a selected folder to a zip archive with the same name.

      • EXPAND_ZIP_ARCHIVE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType EXPAND_ZIP_ARCHIVE
        Expands a zip file into serveral folders and archives

      • MAKE_SITE_PAGE

        public static final ResourceToolAction.ActionType MAKE_SITE_PAGE
        Create a page in the site linking to the content.
